    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-08-31T15:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-08-31T15:40:00-05:00" n="227"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d227">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">674.87/8–2754: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 227<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Iraq</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d227fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_FAD1"
                            >Fritzlan</persName> and cleared by <gloss target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss>
                        and in substance by <gloss target="#t_OFMA1">OFMA</gloss>/OSB. Repeated as
                        telegram 356 to Cairo, 1212 to London, 275 to Ankara, and 278 to
                        Karachi.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-08-31T16:40:00-04:00"
                            >August 31, 1954—4:40 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>119. Cairos 6 to Baghdad<note n="2" xml:id="d227fn2">Not printed; this is the
                        same as telegram 260, which is summarized in <ref target="#d226fn5">footnote
                            5, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> confirms our understanding current Egyptian attitude against
                    association at present with West in area defense arrangements.</p>
                <p>In view Egyptian Government’s apparent rejection <persName corresp="#p_ASN1">Nuri
                        Said</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_SMS1">Saleh Salem</persName> proposals
                    (which could not have been acceptable to <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> in
                    context present orientation <gloss target="#t_ALCSP1">ALCSP</gloss>) Embassy
                    should at appropriate opportunity sound out <persName corresp="#p_ASN1"
                        >Nuri</persName> on his present thinking. Embassy may in its discretion
                    mention Department’s satisfaction over assurance given Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_BBY1">Berry</persName> by <persName corresp="#p_ASN1"
                        >Nuri</persName> re his support for Turk–Pakistan pact (<gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 590)<note n="3" xml:id="d227fn3">
                        <ref target="#d202">Document 202</ref>.</note> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_ASN1">Nuri</persName>’s statement (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 105).<note n="4" xml:id="d227fn4">
                        <ref target="#d223">Document 223</ref>.</note> He not abandoning regional
                    defense principle which he recognized lay behind pact. Having in mind these
                    statements and last paragraph <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 107<note
                        n="5" xml:id="d227fn5">Not printed, but see <ref target="#d226fn3">footnote
                            3, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> we hope <persName corresp="#p_ASN1">Nuri</persName> will
                    focus his attention on Turki-Pakistan pact which we believe offers only basis
                    for realistic and effective defense planning in Near East.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
